Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine in both serum and blood, indicating significant renal dysfunction. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, ketonuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, supporting possible nephrotic syndrome or acute kidney injury. Hemoglobin A1c is low, suggesting no chronic hyperglycemia. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended for further assessment and management of renal impairment and associated metabolic disturbances.
